'''Elias K. Bongmba''' (born 1953) is a [[Cameroon]]ian-[[United States|American]] academic who is an Associate Professor of Religious Studies at [[Rice University]] in [[Houston]], [[Texas]]. His research focuses on African religions. In addition to numerous journal articles he has written two books: *''African Witchcraft and Otherness: A Philosophical and Theological Critique of Intersubjective Relations'' (SUNY Press, 2001). *''The Dialectics of Transformation in Africa'', (Palgrave Macmillan, 2006)
